      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/79/1467",
      "text": [
        ": «لاَ يَنْبَغِي أَنْ تُصَلَّى صَلاَةُ اَلْعِيدَيْنِ فِي مَسْجِدٍ مُسَقَّفٍ وَ لاَ فِي بَيْتٍ إِنَّمَا تُصَلَّى فِي اَلصَّحْرَاءِ أَوْ فِي مَكَانٍ بَارِزٍ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1467 - Ali ibn Ri'ab narrated from Abu Basir from Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) who said:\n\"It is not appropriate for the Eid prayers to be performed in a covered mosque or in a house; rather, they should be prayed in the open air or in an exposed place.\""
        ]
      }
